Key Match Events: Evidence Makgopa scored the first goal for South Africa in the 57th minute
Teboho Mokoena fired in a superb late free-kick for South Africa's second goal in the 5th minute of stoppage time
Achraf Hakimi hit the crossbar with a penalty for Morocco
Sofyan Amrabat was sent off for a professional foul in the late stages of the game
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa's coach praised their team's performance and strategy in containing Morocco's attack
Morocco's coach expressed disappointment and frustration with their team's performance and the missed penalty
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played in the muggy heat of the Laurent Pokou Stadium in Ivory Coast
Morocco's World Cup semi-finalists status was not enough to secure them a win against South Africa
South Africa's win marked their first time past the quarter-finals since 2000
Others: The Africa Cup of Nations continues with Mali facing Ivory Coast in the quarter-finals and South Africa playing Cape Verde
